{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is a generic library for creating and working with ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"concrete","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"syntax trees","type":"text"}]},{"text":" (CSTs).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“Traditional” abstract syntax trees (ASTs) usually contain different","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types of nodes which represent different syntactical elements of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"source text of a document and reduce its information to the minimal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"amount necessary to correctly interpret it. In contrast, CSTs are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"lossless","type":"text"}]},{"text":" representations of the entire input where all tree nodes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are represented homogeneously (the nodes are ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"untyped","type":"text"}]},{"text":") but tagged","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/RawSyntaxKind"},{"text":" to determine the kind of grammatical element","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"they represent.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One big advantage of this representation is that it can recreate the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"original source exactly while also lending itself very well to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"representation of ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"incomplete or erroneous","type":"text"}]},{"text":" trees and is thus highly","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"suited for usage in contexts such as IDEs or any other application","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where a user is ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"editing","type":"text"}]},{"text":" the source text.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The concept and the data structures for Cambium’s syntax trees are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inspired in part by Swift’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift\/tree\/5e2c815edfd758f9b1309ce07bfc01c4bc20ec23\/lib\/Syntax"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and by the Rust ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"library, which itself is a fork of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/rust-analyzer\/rowan\/"},{"text":" developed by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"authors of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/rust-analyzer\/rust-analyzer\/"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Two-layer-storage","type":"heading","text":"Two-layer storage"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Trees consist of two layers:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The inner "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"green tree","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" contains the actual source text as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"position-independent green nodes. Tokens and nodes that appear"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identically at multiple places in the source are deduplicated in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this representation in order to store the tree efficiently. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means that a green tree may structurally be a DAG rather than a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unique object per source position."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To remedy this, the real syntax tree is constructed on top of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"green tree as a secondary tree (called the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"red tree","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":") which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"models the exact source structure."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As a possible third layer, a strongly typed AST can be built on top of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the red tree (see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GettingStarted#AST-Layer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Notable-differences-from-cstree","type":"heading","text":"Notable differences from `cstree`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium tracks ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cstree"},{"text":"’s practical guarantees but uses modern Swift","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"language features rather than imitating Rust mechanically:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Borrowed cursors are the primary traversal API.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" Walking a tree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor"},{"type":"text","text":"s borrowed inside a closure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"scope. There are no per-node retains during traversal, no implicit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"array allocation for child iteration, and no surprise copies of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"red node references. Copyable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle"},{"type":"text","text":"s exist for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"long-lived references but are an explicit opt-in."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Move-only builders, caches, and trees.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenNodeCache"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" are all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"type":"text","text":". Ownership boundaries are visible in the type system;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you cannot accidentally clone a builder or duplicate a parse cache."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Synchronous traversal, ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" snapshots.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Tree navigation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"never goes through an actor. Once a tree is built it can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"promoted to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree\/intoShared()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and freely shared across actors and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tasks.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Witness-based change tracking.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Editing a tree returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" describing the structural change; an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"incremental reparse returns a ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" listing the subtrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that were carried over by reference. Cambium does not bake an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-tracker into the core; consumers translate identities","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through witness chains.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No mutation in place."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Trees are persistent. Editing produces a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"new tree that shares as much green storage with the old as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"possible.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strict serialization."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Snapshots written by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree\/serializeGreenSnapshot()"},{"text":" and read by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumSerialization\/GreenSnapshotDecoder"},{"text":" are length-, hash-, and kind-validated at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"every record. Bad snapshots are rejected with named errors.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Modules","type":"heading","text":"Modules"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is split into several focused modules. Importing the umbrella","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Cambium"},{"text":" module re-exports the runtime modules; test support and macros","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are imported explicitly when you need them. You can also pick individual","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modules directly.","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CambiumCore"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — The foundational layer: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/RawSyntaxKind"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/TextSize"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/GreenNode"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/GreenToken"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CambiumBuilder"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeContext"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenNodeCache"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/LocalTokenInterner"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/SharedTokenInterner"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumIncremental","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseInput","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumAnalysis","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"code":"CambiumAnalysis\/Diagnostic","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"CambiumAnalysis\/SyntaxMetadataStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumASTSupport","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedSyntaxNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedNodeHandle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumOwnedTraversal","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Allocating helpers for handle-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"traversal: "},{"code":"SyntaxNodeHandle.childHandles","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"SyntaxNodeHandle.descendantHandlesPreorder","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumSerialization","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"code":"CambiumSerialization\/GreenSnapshotDecoder","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"serializeGreenSnapshot()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumTesting","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Test-support helpers: "},{"code":"assertRoundTrip(_:equals:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"assertTextLength(_:equals:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"debugTree(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumSyntaxMacros","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"code":"@CambiumSyntaxKind","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"@StaticText","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macros for deriving "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxKind","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift-native concrete syntax tree library inspired by Rust’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Essentials","anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GettingStarted"]},{"title":"Tutorials","anchor":"Tutorials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents"]},{"title":"Sam